Package: cleanTMLE
Title: Staged Clean-Room Causal Analysis with Propensity Score and TMLE Workflows
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Andrew", "Mertens", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "amertens@berkeley.edu"),
    person("cleanTMLE Contributors", role = "ctb"),
    person("M. Alan", "Brookhart", role = c("aut", "cph"),
           comment = "Author of the causalRisk package, whose cohort-specification API and several estimator functions are reused here under MIT licence."),
    person("Alexander", "Breskin", role = c("aut", "cph"),
           comment = "Author of the causalRisk package, whose cohort-specification API and several estimator functions are reused here under MIT licence."),
    person("Bassim", "Eledath", role = c("aut", "cph"),
           comment = "Author of the causalRisk package, whose cohort-specification API and several estimator functions are reused here under MIT licence."))
Description: Provides workflow scaffolding for staged, outcome-blinded
    observational causal analyses. Supports three workflow families:
    conventional propensity-score methods (matching and IPTW),
    fixed-specification targeted minimum loss-based estimation (TMLE),
    and simulation-selected TMLE in which candidate nuisance strategies are
    evaluated on plasmode simulations before real-outcome access. The package
    implements a modular TMLE API with separate functions for fitting the
    treatment mechanism, fitting the outcome mechanism, performing the
    targeting step, and extracting the final estimate, so that each step can
    be executed at the appropriate clean-room stage. The plasmode loop is
    extended with a data-quality stress test ('run_plasmode_dq_stress')
    that evaluates each prespecified TMLE candidate under controlled
    covariate-missingness, treatment-misclassification, outcome-
    misclassification, and unmeasured-confounding scenarios, producing a
    degradation gradient that the GO/FLAG/STOP gate can consume on the same
    scale as the baseline plasmode metrics. SuperLearner ensemble learning
    is the default and recommended propensity-score estimation strategy;
    simpler regression models are also supported. The cohort-specification
    DSL ('specify_models', 'identify_*'), the reporting helpers
    ('make_table1', 'make_table2', 'extreme_weights', 'inspect_ipw_weights',
    'forest_plot'), and the IPW / G-computation / AIPW estimators
    ('estimate_ipwrisk', 'estimate_gcomprisk', 'estimate_aipwrisk',
    'estimate_ipwhr') are reused under MIT-licence attribution from the
    causalRisk package by Brookhart, Breskin, and Eledath. Functions
    unique to cleanTMLE (the analysis lock, outcome masking, plasmode
    feasibility and DQ stress, audit and decision logs, the modular TMLE
    primitives, and the GO/FLAG/STOP gate) are documented as such in the
    individual help pages. Integrates with the 'tmle', 'SuperLearner',
    'survtmle', and 'lmtp' packages for targeted-learning estimation.
